05844nam a22010455i 9783110199024DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20082008gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)703226876  a97831101990247 a10.1515/97831101990242doi  a(DE-B1597)35312  a(OCoLC)646770472  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aP99.4.P72 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a41000aPragmatics and Corpus Linguistics :bA Mutualistic Entente /ced. by Jesús Romero-Trillo. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2008] 4c©2008  a1 online resource (276 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aMouton Series in Pragmatics [MSP] ,x1864-6409 ;v20 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe recent history of linguistics has witnessed the development of some disciplines that were conceived apart but benefited from common intuitions. One example of this phenomenon is the relationship established throughout time between pragmatics and corpus linguistics. Although their arrival heralded the application of two paradigms based on distant theoretical principles, they always showed an interest in their mutual advances and their practical reconciliation gave birth to an intellectual synergy that proved very fruitful. The present volume is a homage to the symbiosis of Pragmatics and Corpus Linguistics and gathers the works of some of the scholars that have striven to create the liaison between them for a better understanding of language.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCorpora (Linguistics). 0aDiscourse analysis. 0aPragmatics. 4aKorpuslinguistik. 4aPragmatik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aPragmatics.  acorpus linguistics.1 aAdolphs, Svenja, econtributor.4ctb4https:/